<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Culture characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Colonies grow on PDA at 25 °C for a week reaching a diameter of 5 cm. Colonies are cotton white in colour, flocculent or velvety, dense, circular, radial. On the reverse, white edge, light yellow in the middle. Not sporulating on OA nor on PDA.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
